    "causal_summary": "Manual query-intelligence scenarios for the Spec Kit Memory system live inside the central playbook and need a phase-specific document that preserves exact prompts, command sequences, evidence expectations, and verdict criteria. Without a dedicated query-intelligence packet, Phase 012 testers must reassemble requirements across the playbook, review protocol, and feature catalog before they can execute or review results. Wave 2-5 additions introduce LLM reformulation, HyDE shadow generation, query surrogates, and query decomposition.",
